stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: Phishing email with CV theme includes malicious Gh0st RAT attachment
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description: On 22 January 2014, a spear phishing email with the subject "Morton, guess the interview result~" was sent from 18602896940@wo.com.cn. The email included the attachment Mckey_Sullivan.rar (MD5: 1fbbc14680eb5bcebfbee461907fcfce) that contained a Narci Gh0st remote administration tool (RAT). If successfully installed, the malware calls back to 210 domains hosted on dynamic DNS sites.

stix:Indicator.indicator:Description:

---- BEGIN EMAIL BODY ---- Hey, Morton
Remember what I said? The girl wearing blue had an outstanding performance at the interview.
I decide to pay her twice as much as working in Yahoo.

rar password: 121035

This attachment contained the malicious file CV_Mckey Sullivan_Compl?cod.exe (MD5: 4a0b37830f93b13e68c1269b79d6c130).

This file was embedded in the attachment Mckey_Sullivan.rar (MD5: 1fbbc14680eb5bcebfbee461907fcfce). It was identified as a Narci Gh0st RAT. The file name uses right-to-left-override to conceal that the file is actually an executable. It calls back to 210 subdomains hosted on dynamic DNS providers.
